{
  "stem": "8.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was so crowded that we could not practically breathe.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I know from other people that there were some pails there for using as a bathroom, or another one for drinking.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't remember seeing them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "All I remember, feeling suffocated and how my mother tried to push me to the window so I could get some air.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And of course, the little children actually suffocated, who could not be held up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was an, an old man who was next to me, and he kind of collapsed.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I recognized him as my neighbor, who I never knew was Jewish, who used to chase us away from front of his house.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But looks like one of his ancestors was Jewish, so he ended up with the same fate as we did.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We traveled for three days.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We didn't know where we were going.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And when the train finally stopped, I saw the sign, Auschwitz-Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I never saw the-- I never heard about the place before.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we were-- the, the doors were unlocked, and we were yelled at by now the German officers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Remember, in Hungary, we were mostly taken care of by the Hungarian gendarmes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But here were the Nazi officers who, with their whips in their hands, with their dogs, they yelled at us, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then there were some prisoners in prisoner garbs who then helped us getting out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We, we were told to line up one after the other, and shoved into a line.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I held on to my mother, but then my cousin, my aunt asked her to hold the baby.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And so my mother held the baby, and I left my mother.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I went with the other younger people.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
